Schlumberger Limited is the world's largest oilfield services company.[2][3] Schlumberger employs approximately 100,000 people[4] representing more than 140 nationalities working in more than 85 countries.[5] Schlumberger has four principal executive offices located in Paris, Houston, London, and the Hague.[6]
Schlumberger is incorporated in Willemstad, Curaçao as Schlumberger N.V.[7] and trades on the New York Stock Exchange, Euronext Paris, the London Stock Exchange, and SIX Swiss Exchange.[8] Schlumberger is a Fortune Global 500 company, ranked 287 in 2016,[9] and also listed in Forbes Global 2000, ranked 176 in 2016.[10]



