Schlumberger - Wikipedia





















 






Schlumberger

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

For the surname, see Schlumberger (surname).

Schlumberger Limited





Type

Naamloze vennootschap (Dutch public company)


Traded as
NYSE: SLB
S&P 100 component
S&P 500 component
Fortune 500


Industry
Oilfield services & equipment


Founded
1926 in France


Founder
Conrad and Marcel Schlumberger


Headquarters
Principal executive offices:
Paris, France
Houston, Texas, US
London, UK
The Hague, Netherlands;
Legal domicile:
Willemstad, Curaçao, Kingdom of the Netherlands



Area served

Worldwide



Key people

Paal Kibsgaard (CEO)


Revenue
 US$ 35.47 billion (2015)[1]



Operating income

 US$ 6.51 billion (2015)[1]



Net income

 US$ 4.29 billion (2015)[1]


Total assets
 US$ 68.0 billion (2015)[1]


Total equity
 US$ 35.9 billion (2015)[1]



Number of employees

100,000


Website
www.slb.com


Schlumberger Limited is the world's largest oilfield services company.[2][3] Schlumberger employs approximately 100,000 people[4] representing more than 140 nationalities working in more than 85 countries.[5] Schlumberger has four principal executive offices located in Paris, Houston, London, and the Hague.[6]
Schlumberger is incorporated in Willemstad, Curaçao as Schlumberger N.V.[7] and trades on the New York Stock Exchange, Euronext Paris, the London Stock Exchange, and SIX Swiss Exchange.[8] Schlumberger is a Fortune Global 500 company, ranked 287 in 2016,[9] and also listed in Forbes Global 2000, ranked 176 in 2016.[10]



