Friday, 21 Apr 2017 10:12am EDT 
April 21 (Reuters) - Schlumberger Nv :Schlumberger says "activity has now reached bottom in all regions" - conf call.Schlumberger says early signs of light offshore work coming in the next couple of quarters.Schlumberger says increase in offshore activity or shallow water activity is probably going to be a second half of the year event, leading into 2018.Schlumberger sees Q2 EPS growth of around 15% to 20% from Q1.Schlumberger expects "solid top line growth" in North America in Q2.Schlumberger says in international markets, still seeing continued pricing pressure on new tenders.Schlumberger says Q1 should be low end of earnings for year in international markets with only limited growth in Q2, but more acceleration in H2. 
			
